snippet.textDisplay:
"You'll have to key all those in?"
Here I am yelling: "MAKE A SHELL SCRIPT!"
Next day... Linus: "Andy found a script"

Newbs, learn to script. :D
The Linux shells are fantastic expanding shells with globs for example. They didn't show enough to see what their initial script they were using was doing but I'm assuming it's mounting the drives and populating /etc/fstab to mount the individual drives within the fs tree at boot. That would take 3 - 5 minutes to make, which includes error checking for invalid parameters and permissions.
snippet.textOriginal:
"You'll have to key all those in?"
Here I am yelling: "MAKE A SHELL SCRIPT!"
Next day... Linus: "Andy found a script"

The Linux shells are fantastic expanding shells with globs for example. They didn't show enough to see what their initial script they were using was doing but I'm assuming it's mounting the drives and populating /etc/fstab to mount the individual drives within the fs tree at boot.
